item.description: If you're going to come out to the world as having a counter-cultural worldview in the 21st Century, one can hardly avoid reference to the late, great Terence McKenna. Although my view of the famous ethnobotanist, student, and shaman of the alchemical foundations of human consciousness has changed over the decades since his many writings changed the way I perceive the nature of the human condition in the cosmos, I can say that his writings and lectures have had more impact on my worldview than any person I never personally met.
